{% extends "layouts/default.twig" %}
{% block content %}
    <div class="container text-content">
        <h2 class="headline--beta">Workshops</h2>

        <p>For the first time ever at WCEU, we’re excited to open the call for workshops. This year we are thrilled to
        offer this new content format to our WCEU audience, and workshops are a great way to level up skills, work with
        fellow WordPressers, and share in-depth knowledge. We are looking forward to receiving workshop applications,
            and making this a new, educational and fun experience for everyone.</p>

        <p>If you need any inspiration to find a good workshop topic, we’re put together a list of ideas below:</p>

        <h3>Development workshops (beginner and intermediate level)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Custom plugin development</li>
            <li>Development environments</li>
            <li>WordPress and Security</li>
            <li>The WordPress Customizer</li>
            <li>Accessibility</li>
            <li>Internationalization</li>
            <li>eCommerce</li>
            <li>Developing a custom WordPress theme</li>
            <li>CSS: CSS Grids, animations, SVG, etc.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Advanced Development workshops</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>The Rest API</li>
            <li>JavaScript</li>
            <li>JS Frameworks (React, Angular, Vue.js, Backbone, etc.)</li>
            <li>OOP (Object Oriented Programming)</li>
            <li>Performance (caching strategies, front-end and backend optimizations, etc.)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Design and UX workshops</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>User Experience</li>
            <li>Design process</li>
            <li>Design thinking</li>
            <li>Customer journey</li>
            <li>Product strategy</li>
            <li>Prototyping</li>
            <li>Users Research / Testing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Community workshops</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Building a local WordPress community</li>
            <li>Speaking at WordCamps</li>
            <li>Best practices to organize a WordCamp</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Content workshops</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Content strategy</li>
            <li>Create compelling content</li>
            <li>Storytelling</li>
            <li>Content planning for multi-language sites</li>
            <li>Publishing</li>
            <li>SEO</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Business workshops</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Running a successful design/dev shop</li>
            <li>Project scoping and estimation</li>
            <li>Find your niche</li>
            <li>SaaS</li>
            <li>Selling online</li>
            <li>Internet law</li>
        </ul>

        {% if cfp_open %}
        <p>
            <a class="btn-opencfp btn-opencfp-medium btn-opencfp--light" href="{{ url('user_new') }}">Apply Now</a>
        </p>
        {% endif %}
    </div>
{% endblock %}

